<br>
All drops?<br>
<br>
Anyone know or are we all just reclicking EQ.exe to see a patch server in fubar hell? <p><p align=left><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/changingtide/images/inpom.jpg><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"You must do the thing you think you cannot do." - Eleanor Roosevelt </font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utauronoftunare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tauron of Tunare</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/4/01 9:22:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> New spells</span><hr size=1> Right now all I could find were the low level group spells (protection of wood, etc) in a fairly hidden place in shadow heaven. Its a large dome made of rock, you go in and step into the teleport pad and it takes you to the vendors. Shaman, ranger and bestlord also found there. No luck finding the good ones yet. Best bet they are all rare drops. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufinvarrasidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Finvarra Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/5/01 3:10:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mistdragons.homestead.com/files/Fin2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> Um...yeah, how truly brilliant of Verant (as if that's suprising)<br>
Putting LOW level druid spells on a vendor up on the moon...so that someone who just started this game and hasn't got mid to high level friends are supposed to get it...how?  <br>
<br>
/boggle <p><img src=http://www.mistdragons.homestead.com/files/Fin1.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidonrufflefuzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidon Rufflefuzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Hobbit of Love</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/5/01 6:02:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> All of the group skin spells are in the druid guild in shadowhaven.  Protection of Nature isn't a bad spell if you aren't 60 yet, group SLN for 700 mana <p><p><center><img src=http://lilyanaeq.homestead.com/files/Signatures/Aidon.jpg>
<BR> <a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24579">Aidon</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/5/01 6:44:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> You don't need any friends to port you up to the moon.  You just go to a spire, buy a ticket, and away you go. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufyrth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fyrth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/5/01 7:47:27 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://fyrth.freewebspace.com/images/S_Fyrth_icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> Ticket is free, at least it was for me in DL last night. No mobs aggroed or were KOS (not even npc necros) all the way from the Nexus/Bazaar/Shadow Haven zones. All the newbie druid needs to do is run to the spires in G Fay (I mean they are a wood elf, right?) and boom, they can go buy their level 1 spells. <br>
<br>
Later,<br>
 <p>Fyrth Pineneedle (55 Preserver) <BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uborreny.showPublicProfile?language=EN>borreny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/5/01 8:16:54 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> I firmly believe that druids got screwed in their bought spells. I didn't bother buying any of them once I saw what they were. Other classes had some actually decent bought spells (even if they were high level), but at level 57, not one of these group &quot;skin like whatever&quot; spells is useful. <p>Borreny 57 Preserver<br>
Visions</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzephaus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zephaus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/6/01 5:34:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> The group skin spells really even aren't all that useful at 51.  I've rarely SLN except when I'm PLing.  Cleric and Pali buffs are always overwriting, so why bother =p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umyth24601.showPublicProfile?language=EN>myth24601</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/7/01 9:57:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> I like the circle SLN.  WHen in many groups now, I tell the cleric that I will handle SLN so they shouln't do Resolution line spells and it saves us a lot of downtime waiting for the cleric to med up. <br>
<br>
Now instead of casting it 6 times (6x300 sheesh) I cast once for 700. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ututtenclawstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tutten Clawstorm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/7/01 1:02:03 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.visi.com/~abros/Tutten_small_wolf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> Resolution is 110 mana.  So even in a full group, it's cheaper for the cleric to cast resolution six times than for us to do protection of nature. :-(<br>
<br>
Of course, it may still be worthwhile to use protection of nature, if the cleric's using more mana than you.  My group tends to do a lot of fear kiting, so the cleric's almost always got more mana than me.<br>
 <p><address>Tutten Clawstorm<br><small><small>Halfling Druid of Druzzil Ro<br>Member of Clan Doomit</small></small></address>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucuchulainekynthelig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuchulaine Kynthelig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/7/01 2:43:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spells</span><hr size=1> SLN (and I assume PON) is better than resolution. <br>
<br>
Once the cleric is 52 and has Herioic Bond though, their's is once again better...and only 400 mana.<br>
<br>
BTW, don't discount the value of PotG with the advent of group Aegolism. Every caster I know (including clerics who can Aego) still wants PoTG over Aegolism. PotG is not only better mana regen, but with Marzin the hitpoints are about the same or better than Aegolism.  <p>Geneze Angelfyre <BR>
Vicar of Tunare<BR>
<a href="mailto:Cuchulaine_eq@hotmail.com">Cuchulaine Kynthelig</a> (reborn!)<BR>
